The paper focuses on implementing deep neural networks in embedded systems, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper specifically addresses the challenge of memory and computation constraints, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for reducing the weights associated with negligible features to zero, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for hardware implementations, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
